Sors quaesturae. The Quaestors drew lota for their respective provinces. Their number increased with the increase of the empire, till from two they became twenty or more. As at first a Quaestoz accompanied each Consul at the head of an army, so afterwards each Proconsul, or Governor of a province, had his Quaestor to col- lect and disburse the revenues of the province. The Quaestorship was the first in the course of Roman honors. It might be entered upon at the age of twenty-four.
